{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205696398/1930110401/0493.xml":{"full_text":"T EDITORIAL PAGE\nOF THE\n[Larger Sites for Elementary\nSchools in D. C.\nWin. V'i\nJJnder the Cramton $16,000,000 loan bill there will be, in a\nffcw yeate, extensive purchases of sites for playgrounds not\nConnected with public school buildings.\nThere should be close co-operation between the Board of\nBfainetinn and the Park and Planning Commission in the pur\nchase of hew playground and school sites and in the purchase\ngs playgrounds that will.be adjacent to existing public school\nbuildings. f\nThe worst shortcoming in many of our public schools is\ntheir lack of sufficient grounds. In the days when land could\nto bought at low prices for school sites opportunities to get\ngbbd acreage were passed. It is now recognised that all\npublic schools should be surrounded by plenty of acreage.\nJt is also widely recognized that public playgrounds should,\nIf possible, be part of school grounds.\n.Schools are constructed to suit population growth and it\nMr out of the question to look many years ahead to where\nfuture school buildings in Washington will be located. If\nthe exact school needs could be forecast school grounds could\nbe bought far ahead and the purchase of playground sites\narranged accordingly. Anyway there should be earnest en\ndeavor on the part of public officials to work together on\nthis problem that schools now without proper playground\nSpace may have better facilities in that direction and that new\nschools may have playground acreage of their own or have\nplayground felicities close by.\n'\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0'\u25a0\u25a0_\nBrain Analyses Will Advance\ni Knowledge of Science\ni\u00bbK|\nThe decision of a distinguished Washington physician to\ngive his brain to scientific analysis immediately after death\nwill contribute toward the unceasing effort of science to find\nmore about this wonderful organ of humanity, the motive\npower behind all human successes and civilization itself.\nThe time will come when sentimentality will not control\ntn matters of this kind and when numerous analyses of active,\nnormal brains will yield tremendous truths toward the build\nbig of a greater civilization and toward the supermen that\nphilosophers and psychologists predict for the future.\nMonkeys have brains, patterned after those of man, but\ntheir mentality is no greater now than when the world began.\nMan\u2019s progress is due to his power to THINK and that\npower comes from the mass of nerve tissue inclosed in the\nMighty little, comparatively, does science know about the\nactual composition and functions of the grey matter that\nconstitutes the brain, and its connections with the spinal\ncord. When more is known mental diseases and'disorders\nmay be minimized and the powers of the healthy brain in\ncreased.\nThat a large percentage of crime is due to physical and\nmental defects is now a certainty. The struggle of pathol\nogists will be to find the causes of these defects. Remedies\nwffl follow.\nt''\nThe Future of Crime\nBy Archibald Henderson\n11\n\u2018No one who gives prolonged\nreflection to the problem of\ncrime and legal treatment\nthereof can fail to be aware\nthatour present codes are\ntainted with the spirit of re\nvenge.\nOrganized society sets up a\nsystem of morals, a code of\nconduct, for the guidance of\nthe individuals constituting\nthat society. The law makes\nhard the way of the trans\ngressor. He must conform to\nthe system, obey the code, 'or\n\u2022take the consequencies. And\nthe consequences may be as\nserious as the crime itself;'\nmurder will be visited by execu\ntion, illegal kidnaping by legal\nkidnaping, theft of goods by\nlegal theft of the person of\nthe thief.\nIt is shocking in the highest\ndegree to realize how lament\nably slow reforms in criminal\ncodes and procedure have been.\nIMB than a century and a\nhklf ago, the death penalty\nwas visited upon the luckless\ncriminal for such slight of\nfences as the theft of five\nshillings\u2019-worth of shop-goods,\n\u2018the robbery of a rabbit-warren,\nand the counterfeiting of reve\nnue perfumery stamps. These\n,are only a few among scores\nOs other slight offences, as\nwe see things today, for which\nthe death penalty was invoked.\nIt was Bacon who said that\nrevenge was a sort of wild jus\ntice. It is possible that so\ncalled justice, if administered\nwith ruthless hand, may appear\n\u25a0to some as a sort of legalized\nrevenge. In the future,'says\nGeorge Godwin in Cain, we\nmay find that by making the\ntest of crime its effect, not\nonly upon the community of\ntoday but also upon the race,\ncertain things now criminal\nwill cease to be so, while others\nnot now crimes will become\noffences.\nNot many years ago; a cer\ntain school of criminologists,\nheaded by the sensational Ital\nian, Cesare Lombroso, advanced\nthe theory that there were cer\nunmistakable stigmata or\nsal marks of the crime\nict. There was, it was\nUrged, a specific criminal type.\nFortunately for human na\nture and the future of the race,\nthis theory has now been ex\nydbded. It is no longer seri\nously entertained by crimin\nologists generally. This does\nfbst mean, however, that there\nis not some association or con\nnection between certain physi\ncal attributes and certain\ntypes of crime.\nLombroso and his followers,'\nin an exact sense,, were taking\na superficial view. They were\nregarding externals, the ap\nparent, physical stigmata. The\ncause, of course, lies deeper\nthan this\u2014namely, in the men\ntal, quirk, the moral twist, the\nabnormal functioning, under\nhigh stress of passion or temp\ntation, of the ordinarily normal\nintelligence.\nLegal punishment must, it is\nargued by many humanitarians,\neliminate from its own nature\nthe taint of retribution. Plato\nsays that the criminal must\nbe adequately punished for the\nsake of deterring others from\ndoing wrong; but in this state\nment Plato overlooks the indi\nvidual criminal himself, upon\nwhom the modem criminologist'\nconcentrates. The criminal\nmust be punished, in order to\ndeter him from repeating his\ncrime or committing other\ncrimes. Punishment, according\nto Bames, can be justified if it\nbrings about moral reforma\ntion. and in future he predicts\nit will be used only in those\ncases where it will be likely to\nhave that effect.\nIf degeneracy is the disease\nof the race, says Godwin, crime\nis the disease of the social\nbody. -He predicts that, in the\nfuture, al lidea. of punishment\nwill be abandoned. The prison\nwill be only a house of deten\ntion* a place where each in\nmate will be studied with the\nsole view of possible mental\nand physical regeneration and\nmoral betterment.\nThe leader in the future treat\nment of crime will not be the\njailer, the turnkey, the warden,\nthe hangman. He will be the\nphysician, the alienist, the psy\nchiatrist, the psychopathologist,\nthe purpose of detention will be\nto diagnose and treat the ills to\nwhich the criminal is subject.\nSome will be treated and bene\nfited; some will be cured and\nrestored to society; others will\nreceive other treatment, accom\nmodated to the individual crim\ninal; sterilization, special types\nof labor and what not. The m-,\ncorrigibles, who will not yield\nto scientific treatment of any\nkind, will be painlessly elim\ninated. through the medium of\nthe lethal chamber. This is the\ntrend of modern opinion.\n(Capyrlghl I*l*. Nawapapar Faatvra\nS*rrtea tee,)\nWA S HIN GZONTIM E S\nSawing Wood By Nelson Harding\nf 4\n[myfhends. 1\u2014\nDEMAND M>EAL OfTK]\nHi-AMENDMENT\nu\n\u2014TMraJm-Tl\nWTTG.O.P PLATFORM 8\nMIHKLWnHB\nTicket\n\u25a0\u25a0l w jflK\n|r\n\n\n/iz-z-\nLetters to the Editor From Readers of The Times\nFiremen Deprived of Work\nAs Emergency Pallbearers\nEditor, Times:\nFalling in line with the sev\neral readers of your paper who\nhave taken the issue of fire\nmen doing outside work up,\nI would like very much to say\nmy piece.\nI am one of the firemen who\ndid funeral work on his off\ntime, which at its very best\nnetted me sl2 per month, as we\ncould only work on the days\nwe were working night work,\nthat constituting two weeks of\nevery month.\nI would like very much for\nthe people of Washington to\nknow that since the firemen\nhave been ordered to stop doing\nthis work it has fallen to the\nlot of; the poor, underpaid\nprinters from the Government\nPrinting Office to do this work,\nand as these men only make\nabout $2,800 per year the Com\nmissioners have completed a\nmaster stroke in aiding the\nunemployment situation in\nWashington. The above state\nment is absolutely based on\nfacts. A PALLBEARER.\nIs Business Depression Due\nTo Decline of Tree Sitters?\nEditor, Times:\nThings certainly are coming\nto a pretty state of affairs\nKNOWLEDGE I\nTEST\nFill each blank:\n1. \u201cMy leaps up when\nI behold a rainbow in the sky.\u201d\n2. \u201cThe best laid o\u2019 mice\nand men gang aft agley.\u201d\n3. \u201cA thing of is a\njoy forever.\u201d\n4. \u201cMore things are wrought\nby\u2014 than this world\ndreams of.\u201d\n5. \u201cThough I speak with the\ntongues of men and and\nhave not charity, I am become\nas sounding brass.\u201d\nMatch correctly:\n6. expect\nquote\n7. cite\ninanimate\n8. answer\nanticipate\n9. lifeless\nsmall\n10. petite\nreply\nDo you know:\n11. What people earliest de\nveloped belief in one god?\n12. What stone is the key to\nEgyptian writing?\n13. With what art is the\nname of Holbein connected?\n14. Os what country was\nPeter the Great king?\n15. With what country do\nyou connect the name of Coper\nnicus?\n(Answers on Magastna Page.)\nI\nwhen we lose our national\n.pride. It seems but a short\n'while ago that the papers of\nour land were loudly singing\nthe praises of tree sitters of\nvarious sorts and species.\nEach community vied with\nits neighbors. Local cham\npionships were established, only\nto be quickly snatched away\nby a more aggressive type of\nindividual\nThen all of a sudden, like\na bolt of lightning from out\nListen, World!\nBy Elsie Robinson\nLon Chaney is dead. Clown,\ncrook, mystic, monster\u2014and in\nprivate life a quiet, somewhat\nmelancholy gentleman \u2014for\nyears he played his \u201cthousand\nfaces\u201d parts. And now he has\ngone. But, in reality, Lon\nChaney still lives on\u2014in each\none of us. For every soul has\na thousand faces and could\n.taste the thrill and delight, the\npower and despair of a thou\nsand lives if it had the courage.\nAlways you have known that\nthis was true of yourself. To\nthe world you have shown one\nface. It was not the face you\nmost preferred. When you\nstarted as a youngster, you\ncertainly didn't plan to look\nor live as you five now. You\nplanned to show quite a dif\nferent sac dramatic, beauti\nful face\u2014thfe fate of a poet or\nan adventurer or a great leader.\nFor the seeds of these other\nlives lay within you. And when\nyou were a child, you did show\nthose other faces. All the sides\nof your soul came and went\nin your dreaming eyes. You\nlearned, slowly and painfully,\nto show only one of your faces\n\u2014that rather dull and stupid\nBill Jones or Maggie Smith\nface which you now wear.\nIt was, as I\u2019ve said, far from\nthe favorite face of your fancy.\nBut\u2014it seemed the most expe\ndient countenance; Your fam\nily expected it. Your boss ex\npected it. And what would\nhave happened if you had re\nfused to wear it? Suppose, in\nstead, you had worn one of your\nother secret, amazing faces?\nOr\u2014worse still\u2014had insisted on\nbeing all your different selves\nin turn? Then what? Then\ncertainly you would have been\nlaughed at, or talked about, or\nprobably despised. You didn\u2019t\ndare to run the risk. And so,\ninstead of showing your \u201cthou\nsand faces\u201d you showed but one\nuntil the world has come\nto believe that you are but one\nperson, that dull, stupid Bill\nJones or Maggie Smith person.\nBut you,, yourself, have al\nways kfiown that you weren\u2019t\njust one. You know that other\nselves come and go within you,\nclamoring for expression. Of\nten, when others think that\nyou are satisfied with your\nof a clear sky, the bottom\ndropped out of the thing just\nwhen it was getting on a pay\ning basis. If you will notice\nyour old files, you will see that\never since the downfall of\ntree-sitters (that Is, the aban\ndonment of the contest) there\nhas been a continual cry of\nbusiness depression and hard\ntimes.\nWhere are we now? If you\nstop to survey conditions, you\nvail realize perhaps for the\nhumdrum lot, you are in a\nfury of rebellion. Often, when\nthey boast of their exploits,\nyour sealed and secret selves\nhammer and hammer to be off\nand away. But you dire not\nshow those secret selves\nfor fear\nAnd with the passage of the\nyears it becomes harder and\nharder to show them, even if\nyou had the courage. For\nfaces harden on us like shells,\nwalling in the living spirits\nthat pluck and peer through\ntheir eyes.\nYou\u2019ve known that your face\nwas becoming a shell and\nyou\u2019ve hated it. In countless\nways you\u2019ve tried to find ex\npression for those other selves.\nYou\u2019ve read detectives stories,\nadventure and confession\nstories, stories of great, success\nful men; beautiful, compelling\nwomen. You\u2019ve read poetry\nand books on farming. Played\npee-wee golf; thought your\n\u2022waistline was a bulging-46!\nAnd you went to see Lon\nChaney\u2014LON CHANEY WHO\nDARED TO SHOW HIS\nTHOUSAND FACES.**\nYou like Lon Chaney, even\nthough he horified you at times.\nYou felt a queen nearness to\nhim. Secretly you envied him\nand had a sneaking notion that\nyou could jolt \u2019em, too, if you\nhad the breaks. You HAVE\nthe breaks\u2014if you\u2019ll use them.\nYou too can show your other\nfaces, live all sides of your\nthousand lives. IF YOU HAVE\nTHE COURAGE. But people\nmay laugh at-you or talk about\nyou? Well, what if they do?\nCould any amount of ridicule or\ngossip be worse than this slow\nsmothering of your soul? What\nif they do think you\u2019re queer?\nYou ARE queer, thank God!\nMake the most of it!\nBut...there are furtive, dark\nfaces in you which you wouldn\u2019t\nwant to show'? There are in\ndeed. And if you\u2019re civilized\nyou\u2019ll hide them, but you won\u2019t\ndeny them. It is well to know\nALL your faces... IF ONLY\n\u2022THAT'YOU MAY BE MORE\n-TOLERANT TOWARD THE\nTWISTED, TERRIBLE FACE\nOF YOUR BROTHER.\n(Copyright, I*3o. by King Faateraa\nSyndicate, lac.) _\nfirst time, that we are in a\nstate of disintegration; no\nyoungsters are being trained\nto follow in the footsteps of\nthe present record holders and\nwhen the present crop dies out.\nI predict a foreign invasion of\n\u201ctree-sitters,\u201d whose families\nhave followed that business for\ngenerations will snatch away\nour laurels.\nAre we going to let minia\nture golf make us forcet?\nA. D. G.\nMARRY-GO\nROUND\nBy Helen Rowland\u2014\u00bb-\nWhere Is \u201cAmerica\u2019s Lover?\"\nWhere are the \u201cIT men\u201d of\nyesteryear?\nWhat has become of all the\nGreat Lovers, who adorned the\nscreen and the stage?\nWhere are the Leo Deitricht\nsteins, the Lou Tellegens, and\nthe William S. Harts? Where\nis the successor to the late\nValentino?\nThere are many great actors\non the screen\u2014more, great\nactors than ever, since the\ntalkies came in. But, where is\n\u201cAmerica\u2019s Lover\"\u2014the movie\nlover once adored by all the\nscreen fans?\nPerhaps I\u2019ve missed him, or\noverlooked him, but, in all the\nplays and photoplays I have\nseen in the last two years,\nthere appear to be only two\nkinds of love-making.\nThe tempestuous, caveman,\ngrab-as-grab-can kind usually\nrelegated to the villian. And\nthe cool, casual, \"Well-what-say\nold girl-let\u2019s-make-a-stab-at-mar\nriage\u201d kind\u2014usually indulged\nin by the hero?\nDoes this mean that women\nare tired of the glamour of\nlove? That they want their\nlove-making either rough, raw,\nand elemental, or in common\nsense walking boots? Because\nactors always give the public\nwhat they WANT.\n.Does it mean that the modern\ngirl doesn\u2019t KNOW any kind of\nlove-making between the wrest\nling-match variety and the pat\non-the-back, good-pal sort?\nDoes it mean that men have\nforgotten how to make love\n\u2014or that women have forgotten\nhow to TAKE it?\nDoes a woman really regard\na football clutch, a primitive\nclinch, and a few savage kisses\nas \u201clove-making\u201d?\nHave all the glory and the\nglamour, all the mystery and\ntenderness, all the ardor and\nromance gone out of love, for\never?\nMust love-making be either\nviolent and frenzied or non\nchalant and commonplace?\nARE we emotionally DEAD?\nI don\u2019t believe it! Human\nnature doesn\u2019t change like that\n\u2014not even in a machine ago!\nWASHINGTON. D. C.,'\nNOVEMBER 4,1930\nWhen You Buy\u2014\nA Radio.\nSBw\u00dff\n\u00ab&fc> Jy\nTHE RADIO\u2014AND THOSE WHO MAKE IT.\nRadio, three or four years ago a luxury, is now a necessity\nin every household.\nIf you have none, and can afford one, the present is a good\ntime to buy.\nNever before were prices so low, or receiving sets so near\nperfection.\nThe family without a radio today might as well b\nmarooned on a desert island, as far as keeping in touch wit?\nthe latest news, the latest opinion, the latest entertainment i\nconcerned. I\nIn these respects, radio has abolished time and space,\nbrought the world to your easy chair.\nNot to take advantage of it is to cut yourself off from the\nera yon live in, like some hermit of the dark ages.\nHermits are of no value to anyone,' including themselves.\nBuy a radio if you can afford it. It is worth the money.\nAnd what you pay will be distributed among many. The\nsketch above shows a few.\nMetal workers, glass workers, cabinetmakers, assemblers,\nartists, performers\u2014all share in the purchase price and spend\ntheir earnings for other products.\nBusiness is stimulated thereby, not only ONE business, but\nALL business. Jobs are created, unemployment is cut down,\ncustomers are made for articles that perhaps YOU sell or\nproduce.\nEconomists estimate that if everybody in the United States\nwould spend five dollars a week more than they have been\nspending for a period of only two weeks, the so-called de\npression would be transformed into a genuine boom.\nFoolish spending is never to be defended.\nWISE spending for necessities or even luxuries will lift\nthe cloud.\nEight Great Men\nHow Many Do You Know!\nBrush off the dust that has settled oyer your memory since\nschool days; ask yourself what you know about these eight\nAen:\nEuclid, Ptolemy, Kepler, Copernicus, Aristotle, Galileo,\nNewton and Einstein.\nBernard Shaw, in his first international broadcast to the\nAmerican people, called these eight men \u201cthe makers of uni\nverses,\u201d and added a still finer tribute \u2014that \u201ctheir hands\nwere not stained with the blood of their fellow-men.\nNapoleon, said Mr. Shaw, is by contrast a puny and sinister\nfigure, for he built only an empire, and killed millions while\nbuilding it.\nUnless you are better informed than most, you have but a\nhazy idea of these eight men.\nEinstein you know, though his theory of relativity you de\nnot understand. Perhaps less than half a dozen scientists now\nliving understand it. You DO understand, however, that i\u00a3\nhas profoundly changed mankind\u2019s conception of time an/\nspace.\nNewton you also know, remembering the story that he dir\ncovered the law of gravitation while lying in an orchard. A)\napple fell on him, made him think.\nEuclid you know well if you went through high school. Hi>\ngeometry probably gave you many a headache.\nThe others are more shadowy.\nAristotle, sometimes called the father of philosophy and\nof deductive reasoning; Galileo, the inventor of the telescope!\nPtolemy, who proved the earth was flat; Copernicus, who\nproved it was not; Kepler, the astronomer and mathematician\n\u2014\u25a0you benefit from their thoughts, though you may not know\ntheir names.\nYou are surprised that Shaw omitted Bacon, father of\nmodern science and inductive reasoning,\nYou are still more surprised that Shaw omitted Shaw.\nWORDS FROM LIPS OF WlSfi MEN\nWhatever the number of a\nman\u2019s friends, there will be\ntimes in his life when he has\none too few, but if he has only\none enemy, he is lucky indeed\nif he has not one too many.\n\u2014BULWER-LYTTON.\nI would rather win honor than\nhonors.\nI would rather have genius\nthan wealth.\nI would rather make my name\nthan inherit It\n\u2014Thackeray.","height":"30236","width":"24147"}}
